e as of late.  Not to say they weren't before, but they seem to be taking the lime light now.  I am making this post in hopes of setting up a new guideline for roatations, that would compensate for all the qualities that seem to desired for a rotation to be set up. This would also eliminate the &quot;time zone advantage&quot;.<br>
<br>
Here is a list of what i have noticed to be of concerns in getting into a previously set up rotation.<br>
<br>
1) The guild attempting to get into the rotation must have a force large enough, and well equipped enough to take down the mob.<br>
<br>
2) Guilds currently in the rotation would prefer that Mob X isn't left up for 5 days, so 10 different guilds can take a whack and see if they have the force to kill it.  This is understandable.  This would mean spawn times would be delayed and the rotation pushed back even further.<br>
<br>
3) To currently get into a rotation you must first kill the mob, and then you will be put in.  This doesn't seem to work (as previously described in other threads).  If X guild is all on pst, and Y guild is mostly gmt, then Y guild will kill Z mob when it is their turn, and long before X guild even logs in. (please note use of gmt and pst are simply the extremes of the time zone and not meant to relate to any guilds involved)<br>
<br>
What i propose is this.<br>
<br>
1) Each guild has a representative with access to the RTA private forums.<br>
<br>
2) Set up a forum in which current rotations may be discussed. If a guild thinks they are of capable force to take down a mob, then they may post there for the ability to do such and obtain a spot in the rotation. <br>
<br>
3) An example:  X guild and Z guild are currently in Zlandicar rotation.  X guild is next in Zlandicar rotation, he is scheduled to spawn in 5 days.  Y guild is not in Zland rotation as of yet, but would like the opportunity to prove themselves.  Y guild puts a post on the forum stating they would like the opportunity to try Zlandicar.  X guild and Z guild must both post stating they agree to let Y guild have one full day to attempt to kill Zlandicar.  Thus both guilds know the rotation will be pushed back a day from the original spawn time if failed. You will only have one day to attempt to kill the Mob.  If Y guild fails to take down Zlandicar then they will not have to oportunity to post for another try until X guild and Z guild have gone thru another full rotation on Zlandicar.  This means if you fail and there are 4 guilds in the rotation, you must wait 4 spawns before applying for another chance.<br>
<br>
4) When a guild applies for a chance to step into a rotation, the only thing that may be considered is the guilds ability to kill the mob. This will be based upon previous accomplishments of said guild.  Faction may not be considered. A mob is a mob is a mob.  The best example i can think of would be a giant aligned guild killing Dozecar.  If they applied to do such, then faction would not be the question, but the ability to kill the mob would be the question.  <br>
<br>
I do realize that some guilds will not like the idea of this, simply because it breaks away from what is currently in place on the Rathe, and some dislike change.  This forum would give all guilds the ability to kill all mobs currently on rotation without judgement of faction, stepping on toes etc.  It is essentially the fairest way to go about it.  Giving all a fair chance, regardless of guild, faction, status, and simply being based upon previous accomplishments.<br>
<br>
I request that you only post on this thread if you have a productive comment, or one that may help make The Rathe a better place to come and spend your free time.<br>
<br>
Sincerely, <br>
<br>
