<br>
Instead, why not have a guild request to attempt the mob and be added to the end of the rotation for one attempt?  If you succeed, that is your place in line from then on, if not then you have to wait out a round before asking again.  Only put one new guild between 2 established guilds also.<br>
<br>
That way no one guild is singled out and never has to wait more than one spawn.  Sort of the Trak model with rules for joining that isn't in place now.  No one could scream bias or discrimination that way either.<br>
<br>
*edit: if a guild is going to try something they know they cannot handle, then they have bigger problems than just failing.<br>
